cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DL

This paper is about neural machine translation (NMT) and proposes a new vocabulary reduction method that considers the morphological properties of the language. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper uses unsupervised morphology learning and supervised morphological analysis, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also evaluates the proposed method in terms of translation accuracy, which is a common metric in natural language processing and neural networks (cs.NE, cs.DL).
